  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\r\nAfter a long period of non-finalisation ends, if Teku is running in archive mode, it may need to replay a significant number of blocks to generate the states to store in the finalized database. Currently this is done synchronously before the store transaction can commit, blocking further updates.\r\n\r\nThe generation should happen asynchronously, allowing Teku to continue tracking chain head while the states are backfilled into the finalised database.",
